<geoCoordinate id="BBD94AD51535BFDFD325F6CFB5C76DBD" degrees="32.40583" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="1" value="32.40583">32.40583Â°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="283CDDE355E93E1681798DB02901A988" degrees="67.15888" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="67.15888">67.15888Â°E</geoCoordinate>
, sandy railway bank, 5.08.2011, 
<emphasis id="0953EC6A1BE91747B6F65D826B7A83E0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166">P. Uotila</emphasis>
49222 (H 824080).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3F123733E15BCABD97ABC91300D8169B" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166" type="pathways of introduction">
<paragraph id="CC0CBB32DFDDF0649F64B9FA448D01D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166">Pathways of introduction</paragraph>
<paragraph id="088BCF1B16033F61D8CA9B78A798C4F0" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166">Transport - Stowaway: Vehicles (car, train).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="26D437DB2E756369844E3E465E97DA7E" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166" type="period of introduction">
<paragraph id="F9DE26B6F3502EE89B675DBE117E2989" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166">Period of introduction</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C6F1144D9C0543E8CC07EC29EF459277" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166">Russia (after 1991).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="826A26900AE45986E4DC9035145F265E" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166">This species was recorded from the place with intense transport activity, in current use. Its very recent introduction is therefore beyond doubt.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F2F4E9ADBCEA87D03A983BD2741BDFE0" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166" type="invasion status">
<paragraph id="79FE465A4365904BC567CAFB9E37C4D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166">Invasion status</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB3CCA2B9C8AED8D952B2729CB60305F" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166">Only a few individuals were observed. The collector's notes suggested a casual occurrence.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="707388C6A523909EC24C82789453A53D" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="31EC17282ADC971A3020DBBB98D9F060" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5F3F6448DBD5F1354D2F230024E09421" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166">Open places, river sands, disturbed grasslands.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BF597CCE6D93E3277CE8044D935B6CA5" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166" type="biology">
<paragraph id="21F799B6DA64899FFD969492C7BF3E46" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166">Biology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="67E7340081D20D3DEC81DB11982E670A" pageId="0" pageNumber="78166">Annual (or overwintering biennial). Therophyte with taproot.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
